## Cross-Cutting Code Rules

- **Type annotations + PEP 257 docstrings** on every Python function
- **No `frappe.db.commit()` in `doc_events`** handlers — breaks atomicity
- **No f-string interpolation in `frappe.db.sql`** — use `values=` parameter binding
- **Justify every `ignore_permissions=True`** with a 1-line comment
- **Default `@frappe.whitelist()` is per-user**; `allow_guest=True` requires rate-limit + signature verification
- **DRY:** search the codebase before writing a new utility; Frappe has many helpers under `frappe.utils.*`

